{"flatpakAppId":"org.gnome.Recipes.desktop","name":"Recipes","summary":"GNOME loves to cook","description":"\n    <p>\n       Recipes is an easy-to-use application that will help you to discover what to cook\n       today, tomorrow, the rest of the week and for your special occasions.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n       Recipes comes with a collection of recipes that have been collected by GNOME contributors\n       from all over the world. It also lets you store your own recipes and share them with your\n       friends.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n       The major features of Recipes include:\n    </p>\n    <ul>\n      <li>Add and edit your own recipes</li>\n      <li>Share recipes with your friends</li>\n      <li>Export and print shopping lists</li>\n      <li>Adjust quantities based on the number of servings</li>\n      <li>Mark recipes to cook later or add them to your favorites</li>\n      <li>Add notes to recipes</li>\n      <li>Hands-free cooking instruction mode</li>\n    </ul>\n  ","developerName":"Matthias Clasen and others","projectLicense":"GPL-3.0-or-later","homepageUrl":"https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Recipes","donationUrl":"https://www.gnome.org/friends","translateUrl":"https://wiki.gnome.org/TranslationProject","bugtrackerUrl":"https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/recipes/issues/","helpUrl":null,"categories":[{"name":"Utility"}],"downloadFlatpakRefUrl":"gnome-recipes","currentReleaseVersion":"2.0.4","currentReleaseDescription":null,"iconDesktopUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Recipes.desktop/4359077c91c768cf77e65c5d8de261e0/icons/128x128/gnome-recipes_org.gnome.Recipes.png","iconMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Recipes.desktop/4359077c91c768cf77e65c5d8de261e0/icons/128x128/gnome-recipes_org.gnome.Recipes.png","screenshots":[{"thumbUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jammy/org/gnome/Recipes.desktop/4359077c91c768cf77e65c5d8de261e0/screenshots/image-1_224x215.png","imgMobileUrl":"https://appstream.ubuntu.com/media/jamm